properties.headline: High Wind Warning issued January 31 at 1:27PM MST until February 2 at 3:00AM MST by NWS Riverton WY
properties.description:
...High Wind Warning and Watches across portions of northern and
central Wyoming Tonight through Saturday Night...

.Strong winds aloft and a tight pressure gradient will combine for
high winds across the Cody Foothills and Absaroka Mountains
tonight into Saturday. The strong winds will last across the
Absaroka Mountains through Saturday night. A tight pressure
gradient will also result in strong to possibly high wind across
southeast Fremont into Natrona County Saturday and Saturday night.

* WHAT...West to northwest winds 30 to 50 mph with gusts up to 75
mph.

* WHERE...Absaroka Mountains.

* WHEN...Until 3 AM MST Sunday.

* IMPACTS...Mainly to transportation. Extreme blow over risk for
light and high profile vehicles along Chief Joseph Highway.

* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...Areas of blowing snow will also occur with
severely reduced visibility.
properties.instruction:
Use caution if traveling. Please keep two hands on your steering
wheel in case of a sudden, strong wind gust.

NWSheadline: HIGH WIND WARNING IN EFFECT UNTIL 3 AM MST SUNDAY
